<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center">Rental management shouldn't be this hard</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"center","className":"lb-subtitle"} -->
<p class="has-text-align-center lb-subtitle">Most landlords still rely on spreadsheets, scattered emails, and disconnected tools to run their rental business. It creates chaos, missed payments, and wasted time.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:html -->
<div class="lb-problem-grid">

  <div class="lb-problem-card">
    <div class="lb-icon">📊</div>
    <h3>Spreadsheet overload</h3>
    <p>Tracking rent, leases, and expenses across spreadsheets leads to errors and lost data.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="lb-problem-card">
    <div class="lb-icon">📧</div>
    <h3>Scattered communication</h3>
    <p>Tenant messages, maintenance requests, and vendor coordination happen across too many channels.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="lb-problem-card">
    <div class="lb-icon">⏱️</div>
    <h3>Manual everything</h3>
    <p>No automation means hours spent on repetitive tasks that should happen on their own.</p>
  </div>

</div>
<!-- /wp:html -->

</div>
